com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface MessageContext

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DecimalList.ListElementFactory, ExpressionValuesFactory, MutableStringFactory, Recyclable, StringList.ListElementFactory, VariableContainer, VariableFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageContextImpl

    public interface MessageContext
extends ExpressionValuesFactory, StringList.ListElementFactory, DecimalList.ListElementFactory, VariableFactory, VariableContainer, Recyclable
    Instances of this interface are used to associate transient contextual information with a message.

    A message context also serves as a factory for expression values when an expression is evaluated against the containing message.

      • getVariable

        Returns the variable with the given name.
        Parameters:

      • removeVariable

        boolean removeVariable(AsciiStringView name)
        Removes a variable.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the variable to remove
        Returns:
        true if the variable was removed, false otherwise (which indicates that the given name was not the name of an existing variable)

      • forEachVariable

        void forEachVariable(MessageContext.VariableFilter filter,
                     ProcedureZero<AsciiStringView> procedure)
        Executes the given procedure on each variable that matches certain criteria.
        Parameters:
        filter - expresses the criteria defining which variables should be processed. May be null, in which case no filtering is performed
        procedure - the procedure to execute on each variable
